# Project Rules for Cursor AI Agent

## Code Quality
- After making any changes to files, always run `whitespace -r` to clean up trailing whitespace
- When creating or modifying files, ensure proper formatting and whitespace handling

## File Operations
- When writing new files or editing existing files, follow up with whitespace cleanup
- Use the terminal command tool to run `whitespace -r` after file modifications

## Git Commands
- ALL git commands MUST include --no-pager flag BEFORE the subcommand to prevent terminal hanging
- Example: `git --no-pager status` instead of `git status`
- This applies to ALL git operations in the codebase

## Automation
- Remember to execute whitespace cleanup as part of the development workflow
- This helps maintain consistent code formatting across the project
